            <p className="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Circuit of The Americas is built on expansive clay soil that shifts with temperature and moisture. This has created severe bumps and undulations, particularly in key braking zones and corner entries. The surface continues to deteriorate each year despite resurfacing efforts.
            </p>
