                <div>
                  <div className="font-bold">More Wing (High Downforce)</div>
                  <div className="text-sm text-gray-600">Faster in Sector 1, slower on straight</div>
                </div>
                <div className="text-right">
                  <div className="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">-8 kph</div>
                  <div className="text-xs text-gray-500">trap speed penalty</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div className="flex items-center justify-between bg-red-50 p-4 rounded">
                <div>
                  <div className="font-bold">Less Wing (Low Downforce)</div>
                  <div className="text-sm text-gray-600">Faster on straight, slower in Sector 1</div>
                </div>
                <div className="text-right">
                  <div className="text-2xl font-bold text-red-600">-0.3s</div>
                  <div className="text-xs text-gray-500">Sector 1 penalty</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="flex items-center justify-between bg-green-50 p-4 rounded border-2 border-green-500">
                <div>
                  <div className="font-bold">Optimal Efficiency (L/D ≥3.2)</div>
                  <div className="text-sm text-gray-600">Balanced performance everywhere</div>
                </div>
                <div className="text-right">
                  <div className="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">Best Lap</div>
                  <div className="text-xs text-gray-500">320+ kph AND fast S1</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-gray-700 text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h4 className="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Race Strategy Implications</h4>
            <p className="text-sm mb-3">
              High drag efficiency unlocks strategic flexibility:
            </p>
            <div className="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <span className="mr-3">→</span>
                <span>Can defend into Turn 12 hairpin knowing you won't lose position back on the straight</span>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <span className="mr-3">→</span>
                <span>Alternative passing opportunities beyond just DRS on back straight</span>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <span className="mr-3">→</span>
                <span>Can run higher downforce for tire management without strategic penalty</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      )
    },
    {
      title: "Pillar 3: Technical Breakdown",
      subtitle: "Four Key Components",
      type: "content",
      content: (
        <div className="space-y-6">
          <div className="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-xl mb-3">Integrated Efficiency Parameters</h3>
            
            <div className="space-y-4">
              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-600">
                <div className="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Core L/D Ratio</div>
                <p className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  The fundamental efficiency metric. Target ≥3.2 means for every unit of drag, you generate at least 3.2 units of downforce. Achieved through clean flow management, optimized wing profiles, and minimal separation.
                </p>
                <div className="bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded text-xs">
                  <div className="font-bold mb-1">Key Design Areas:</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Wing profile optimization (avoiding excessive camber)</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Body shaping to minimize pressure drag</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Floor/diffuser efficiency maximization</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-600">
                <div className="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Rear Stability in Yaw</div>
                <p className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  Texas wind is unpredictable. The rear wing and diffuser must maintain stable downforce with ±8° of yaw angle (crosswind). Poor yaw stability forces conservative setup, sacrificing straight-line speed for safety margin.
                </p>
                <div className="bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded text-xs">
                  <div className="font-bold mb-1">Design Solutions:</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Rear wing endplate geometry managing crosswind flow</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Diffuser sidewall vortex generators stabilizing expansion</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Beam wing contribution reducing rear wing sensitivity</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-600">
                <div className="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Tire Wake Management</div>
                <p className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  Front tire wakes create turbulent, high-drag air that hits the rear wing. Poor wake management can cost 15% rear wing efficiency. Bargeboards and floor edges must channel this air away from critical surfaces.
                </p>
                <div className="bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded text-xs">
                  <div className="font-bold mb-1">Design Solutions:</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Floor edge wing vortices pushing tire wake outboard</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Sidepod undercut directing clean air to rear wing</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Front wing Y250 vortex management</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-600">
                <div className="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Cooling Drag Budget</div>
                <p className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  Austin temperatures (25-35°C) require significant cooling. Every square centimeter of radiator inlet creates drag. Target: keep cooling drag below 8% of total drag through efficient heat exchanger sizing and bodywork integration.
                </p>
                <div className="bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded text-xs">
                  <div className="font-bold mb-1">Design Solutions:</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Optimized inlet sizing (not oversized for worst case)</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Efficient radiator exit management reducing base drag</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-700">• Sidepod shaping to minimize separation from outlets</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-gray-800 text-white p-4 rounded-lg">
            <div className="font-bold mb-2">Validation Metric</div>
            <p className="text-sm">
              Within 8 kph of fastest trap speed while maintaining top-3 Sector 1 performance. This proves the package hasn't sacrificed one for the other.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      )
    },
    {
      title: "Design Priorities",
      subtitle: "Ranking for COTA Specifically",
      type: "content",
      content: (
