              </div>
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <span className="font-bold mr-3 text-gray-700">Speed Trace Delta:</span>
                <span>Compare our acceleration out of T11 vs competitors. If they pull away immediately, they have better low-speed platform.</span>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <span className="font-bold mr-3 text-green-600">Trap Speed Pattern:</span>
                <span>If trap speed improves as fuel burns off, we have good efficiency. If it stays flat or worsens, ride height sensitivity issue.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-gray-800 text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h4 className="font-bold text-lg mb-3">GPS Comparison Priorities</h4>
            <div className="text-sm space-y-2">
              <div>1. <span className="font-bold">Turn 3-6 speed overlay:</span> Direct measure of high-speed downforce consistency</div>
              <div>2. <span className="font-bold">Turn 11 exit to T12 entry:</span> Low-speed platform and acceleration efficiency</div>
              <div>3. <span className="font-bold">Turn 19-20 stability:</span> Final high-speed test of complete package</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      )
    },
    {
      title: "Decision Framework",
      subtitle: "When Compromises Are Necessary",
      type: "content",
      content: (
        <div className="space-y-6">
          <div className="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-red-600">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-xl mb-4 text-red-900">If Ride Height Robustness Fails</h3>
            <div className="space-y-3">
              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Symptom: Porpoising or unpredictable behavior</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  <span className="font-bold">Decision:</span> Raise ride height immediately, accept 2-3% downforce loss everywhere. Cannot race an unpredictable car.
                </div>
                <div className="text-xs bg-red-50 p-2 rounded">
                  Impact: Lose 0.3-0.4s per lap but finish the race. Unpredictable car costs more and risks DNF.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Symptom: Excessive plank wear in practice</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  <span className="font-bold">Decision:</span> Raise 1-2mm, optimize wing angles to recover some downforce. Disqualification for plank wear is unacceptable risk.
                </div>
                <div className="text-xs bg-red-50 p-2 rounded">
                  Impact: Small performance loss but guaranteed legal car at race end.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-blue-600">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-xl mb-4 text-blue-900">If Downforce Consistency Issues</h3>
            <div className="space-y-3">
              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Symptom: Understeer in slow corners, oversteer in fast</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  <span className="font-bold">Decision:</span> Adjust wing angles to optimize for driver confidence in most critical corners (prioritize Sector 1).
                </div>
                <div className="text-xs bg-blue-50 p-2 rounded">
                  Impact: Accept slightly suboptimal balance in less critical sections for overall consistency.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Symptom: Front wing stalling at low speeds</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  <span className="font-bold">Decision:</span> Reduce front wing angle, add rear wing to maintain balance. Sacrifice some peak downforce for consistency.
                </div>
                <div className="text-xs bg-blue-50 p-2 rounded">
                  Impact: Lower absolute downforce but more predictable platform. Driver confidence improves, lap times may actually improve.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-gray-600">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-xl mb-4 text-gray-900">If Drag Efficiency Issues</h3>
            <div className="space-y-3">
              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Symptom: 12+ kph trap speed deficit</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  <span className="font-bold">Decision:</span> Reduce rear wing angle by 1-2°. Must protect against DRS trains and strategic vulnerability.
                </div>
                <div className="text-xs bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded">
                  Impact: Lose 0.1-0.15s in Sector 1, gain 5-7 kph trap speed. Net benefit in race due to passing/defending capability.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Symptom: Rear instability in crosswinds</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
                  <span className="font-bold">Decision:</span> Add small gurney flap (+3-5mm) to rear wing. Prioritize driver confidence over absolute drag.
                </div>
                <div className="text-xs bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded">
                  Impact: Lose 2-3 kph but car becomes raceable in all conditions. Safety and consistency trump marginal speed gain.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-yellow-600 mt-6">
            <h4 className="font-bold text-yellow-900 mb-2">Golden Rule</h4>
            <p className="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Never compromise on safety or legality. Between the three pillars, ride height robustness is non-negotiable. Between consistency and efficiency, always choose consistency - a predictable slower car beats an unpredictable fast car over race distance.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      )
    },
    {
      title: "Communication Strategy",
      subtitle: "Keeping Everyone Aligned",
      type: "content",
      content: (
        <div className="space-y-6">
          <div className="bg-blue-900 text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-xl mb-4">Driver Briefing - Key Messages</h3>
            <div className="space-y-3 text-sm">
              <div className="bg-blue-800 p-3 rounded">
                <div className="font-bold mb-1">What to Expect</div>
                <div className="text-blue-100">
                  "The car should feel planted through Turn 1 and the high-speed esses. If you feel inconsistency between laps, especially on bumps, tell us immediately - that's our priority fix."
                </div>
              </div>
              <div className="bg-blue-800 p-3 rounded">
                <div className="font-bold mb-1">What We Need From You</div>
                <div className="text-blue-100">
                  "Rate predictability 1-10 in three zones: high-speed Sector 1, slow corners (T11, T15), and bumpy sections. We need this every session to validate our aero platform."
                </div>
              </div>
              <div className="bg-blue-800 p-3 rounded">
                <div className="font-bold mb-1">Trade-offs</div>
                <div className="text-blue-100">
                  "We may not be fastest on the back straight, but you should be confident defending into Turn 1 and attacking into Turn 12. Our philosophy is balanced performance, not peak in one area."
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-xl mb-4">Engineering Debrief Structure</h3>
            <div className="space-y-4">
              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-600">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Post-FP1 (30 minutes)</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700">
                  1. Validate ride height: any floor strikes, porpoising, or plank wear concerns?<br/>
                  2. Driver confidence scores: does real-world match predictions?<br/>
                  3. Telemetry correlation: ride height behavior vs downforce consistency<br/>
                  4. Go/no-go decision: is baseline philosophy correct or do we need major changes?
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-red-600">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Post-FP2 (45 minutes)</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700">
                  1. Long run analysis: performance degradation with fuel burn-off<br/>
                  2. Competitive benchmarking: where are we losing/gaining vs top 3?<br/>
                  3. Setup optimization: wing angles, ride height fine-tuning<br/>
                  4. Lock in race configuration or continue development in FP3?
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-green-600">
                <div className="font-bold mb-2">Post-FP3 (20 minutes)</div>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-700">
                  1. Final configuration confirmation<br/>
                  2. Qualifying strategy: one-lap vs race setup compromise<br/>
                  3. Weather/wind forecast: any last-minute adjustments needed?<br/>
                  4. Contingency plans: what changes can we make during race if needed?
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-yellow-600">
            <h4 className="font-bold mb-2">Team Principal Updates</h4>
            <p className="text-sm text-gray-700">
              After each session, provide three-line summary: (1) Are all three pillars performing to target? (2) What is our competitive position? (3) Any risks or concerns? Keep it concise and actionable.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      )
    },
    {
      title: "Summary & Action Items",
      subtitle: "Executive Overview",
      type: "content",
      content: (
        <div className="space-y-6">
          <div className="bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-800 to-gray-900 text-white p-8 rounded-lg">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-3xl mb-6">Three Pillars for COTA Success</h3>
            
            <div className="space-y-4">
              <div className="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div className="bg-red-600 rounded-full w-10 h-10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-xl font-bold">1</div>
                <div>
                  <div className="font-bold text-xl">Ride Height Robustness</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-300 text-sm">Floor must work across 8-12mm heave range without stalling. Non-negotiable for COTA's bumps.</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div className="bg-blue-600 rounded-full w-10 h-10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-xl font-bold">2</div>
                <div>
                  <div className="font-bold text-xl">Downforce Consistency</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-300 text-sm">Platform stable from 80-280 kph with minimal balance shift. Critical for driver confidence.</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div className="bg-gray-600 rounded-full w-10 h-10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-xl font-bold">3</div>
                <div>
                  <div className="font-bold text-xl">Drag Efficiency</div>
                  <div className="text-gray-300 text-sm">L/D ≥3.2 enabling balanced performance without strategic compromises.</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div className="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-green-600">
              <h4 className="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-green-900">Success Looks Like</h4>
              <div className="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                <div>✓ Sector 1 within 0.15s of fastest</div>
                <div>✓ Trap speed within 8 kph of fastest</div>
                <div>✓ Consistent times across fuel loads</div>
                <div>✓ Driver confidence ≥8/10</div>
                <div>✓ No plank wear concerns</div>
                <div>✓ Flexible race strategy options</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div className="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-red-600">
              <h4 className="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-red-900">Failure Modes to Avoid</h4>
              <div className="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                <div>✗ Porpoising or floor strikes</div>
                <div>✗ Unpredictable handling</div>
                <div>✗ Excessive trap speed deficit</div>
                <div>✗ Performance degradation with fuel</div>
                <div>✗ Plank wear illegality</div>
                <div>✗ Driver confidence issues</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-blue-900 text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-xl mb-4">Immediate Action Items</h3>
            <div className="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <div className="bg-blue-700 rounded px-3 py-1 mr-3 text-xs font-bold">WEEK -6</div>
                <div>Complete CFD sensitivity studies for all three pillars. Present findings to aero team.</div>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <div className="bg-blue-700 rounded px-3 py-1 mr-3 text-xs font-bold">WEEK -4</div>
                <div>Wind tunnel validation program. Confirm targets are achievable with current package.</div>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <div className="bg-blue-700 rounded px-3 py-1 mr-3 text-xs font-bold">WEEK -2</div>
                <div>Manufacturing contingency parts. Brief driver on expected characteristics and feedback needs.</div>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <div className="bg-blue-700 rounded px-3 py-1 mr-3 text-xs font-bold">FP1</div>
                <div>Validate baseline. Critical ride height assessment through Turn 1 and Turn 9 bumps.</div>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-start">
                <div className="bg-blue-700 rounded px-3 py-1 mr-3 text-xs font-bold">FP2</div>
                <div>Optimization phase. Lock in race configuration if all targets met. Identify any required compromises.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-600 to-green-700 text-white p-8 rounded-lg text-center">
            <div className="text-3xl font-bold mb-3">Clear Targets. Measurable Outcomes.</div>
            <div className="text-xl text-green-100">Execute the plan. Win on Sunday.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      )
    }
  ];

  const nextSlide = () => {
    if (currentSlide < slides.length - 1) {
      setCurrentSlide(currentSlide + 1);
    }
  };

  const prevSlide = () => {
    if (currentSlide > 0) {
      setCurrentSlide(currentSlide - 1);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-gray-800 to-black p-8">
      <div className="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        {/* Slide Counter */}
        <div className="text-white text-sm mb-4 flex justify-between items-center">
          <div>Slide {currentSlide + 1} of {slides.length}</div>
          <div className="text-gray-400">{slides[currentSlide].title}</div>
        </div>

        {/* Main Slide */}
        <div className="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-2xl p-12 min-h-[600px] flex flex-col">
          <div className="mb-8">
            <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
              {slides[currentSlide].title}
            </h1>
            <div className="text-xl text-gray-500">
              {slides[currentSlide].subtitle}
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="flex-1">
            {slides[currentSlide].content}
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Navigation */}
        <div className="flex justify-between items-center mt-6">
          <button
            onClick={prevSlide}
            disabled={currentSlide === 0}
            className={`flex items-center space-x-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold transition-all ${
              currentSlide === 0
                ? 'bg-gray-700 text-gray-500 cursor-not-allowed'
                : 'bg-red-600 text-white hover:bg-red-700'
            }`}
          >
            <ChevronLeft size={20} />
            <span>Previous</span>
          </button>

          <div className="flex space-x-2">
            {slides.map((_, index) => (
              <button
                key={index}
                onClick={() => setCurrentSlide(index)}
                className={`w-3 h-3 rounded-full transition-all ${
                  index === currentSlide
                    ? 'bg-red-600 w-8'
                    : 'bg-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-500'
                }`}
              />
            ))}
          </div>

          <button
            onClick={nextSlide}
            disabled={currentSlide === slides.length - 1}
            className={`flex items-center space-x-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold transition-all ${
              currentSlide === slides.length - 1
                ? 'bg-gray-700 text-gray-500 cursor-not-allowed'
                : 'bg-red-600 text-white hover:bg-red-700'
            }`}
          >
            <span>Next</span>
            <ChevronRight size={20} />
          </button>
        </div>

        {/* Quick Jump */}
        <div className="mt-6 text-center text-gray-400 text-sm">
          Use dot navigation or arrow keys to jump between slides
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default AeroDeck;
